Berkshire Hathaway Share Traded 49% Above Close on Nasdaq

-- B y   N i k o l a j   G a m m e l t o f t   a n d   C e c i l e   V a n n u c c i
-- 
2011-02-28T21:07:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/berkshire-hathaway-share-traded-49-above-close-on-nasdaq-1-.html
A share of  Berkshire Hathaway Inc .
changed hands on the Nasdaq Stock Market at $189,999 in trading
before the official open of U.S. exchanges today, 49 percent
above the Feb. 25 close.  The company’s Class A stock jumped to $189,999 at 7:21 a.m.
in New York, after closing at $127,550 on Feb. 25. There were no
additional trades before the shares opened at 9:30 a.m. at
$129,000, according to Bloomberg data. They climbed 2.9 percent
to $131,300 as of 4 p.m.  Berkshire Hathaway said on Feb. 26 that quarterly profit
rose 43 percent to the highest since 2007 on derivative gains
and earnings from Burlington Northern Santa Fe that billionaire
Chairman  Warren Buffett  bought last year. Fourth-quarter net
income advanced to $4.38 billion, or $2,656 a share, from $3.06
billion, or $1,969, a year earlier, Omaha, Nebraska-based
Berkshire said.  Alexandra Honeysett, a Nasdaq spokeswoman, declined to
comment. NYSE Euronext’s Jill Archibald also declined to
comment.  To contact the reporters on this story:
